I don't think `ty::Foreign` should return false because there is nothing non-const-droppy about them. You cannot have custom drop impls for them i.e. the following would fail:

```rust
#![feature(extern_types)]
extern "C" {
    type Foo;
}

impl Drop for Foo {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        // side effect
    }
}
```

As for "do we ever encounter this type when checking for const Drop?" I'd say not currently, but if we were to introduce const heap it might become possible:

```rust
#![feature(extern_types)]
extern "C" {
    type Foo;
}

fn dropbox(_x: Box<Foo>) {}
```

